v.围攻，困扰 【英】 v.围攻，困扰(to overwhelm, harass, or beset) 【记】 be+siege(围攻)→围 攻；siege本身是一个 单词 【例】 He was besieged by doubts. v. (被敌人)包围; (被询问等)纠缠, 强求 = overwhelm = harass = beset 【例】I was besieged by problems 我为难题所困Troy was besieged by the Greeks 特洛伊城被希腊人围攻. 【记】be被动, siege(n 围攻, 围城) 【记】be + siege；Siege side + edge，四周包围；be + seize 被抓住，捕获→被包围，围攻而抓住；音：被塞挤，被敌人塞挤围攻 besiege (v.)  c.1300, from be- + siege. Related: Besieged; besieging.
